<TITLE> Sixth Softexpo slated for January </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 11 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Association of Software and Information Services has announced it will hold its sixth trade fair from Jan 27 to 31 next year. In a press conference at the Hotel Sonargaon Saturday, BASIS director MA Mubin Khan said the upcoming Softexpo would attract around 200 local and foreign organisations, and more than one lakh visitors were expected to attend. Companies from some 10 countries will participate in the Softexpo this year, said Khan. According to BASIS, the software and Information services sectors are now the second largest graduate employer in the country; with more than 12,000 information technology professional working in more than 500 IT related firms. Bangladesh is now exporting software and information technology services to more than 30 countries, which every year accounts for foreign currency earnings of around Tk 200 crore, the press conference was told. The theme of this year's Softexpo will be the link between man and technology. bdnew
